wikipedia_page.main: Ira Banerjee (born 1 July 1997) is a former English badminton player who competed in international level events. Her highest achievement was winning two silver medals at the 2014 European U17 Badminton Championships in Ankara in the women's singles and doubles competing alongside Jessica Pugh. She is also a double English U17 women's singles champion.
